Subject: Re: [T2] removing rusty shock sleeve from mounting bolt

On Sun, 11 Apr 2004 VWBrain(-at-)aol.com wrote:

> Hello Guys   I,m guessing Joel doesnt have air power here  so heat ,
> pentrating stuff prefer PB blaster,  will help. Try vise grips and hiting with a
> hammer or a chisel and hammer  later and have fun  Mark Dearing

I've had luck with BIG vise-grips.  Just clamp then onto the sleeve
tightly enough to leave grooves in the sleeve.  Unclamp.  Repeat at a
different location.  The goal is to end up with a bunch of grooves all
around the sleeve.  Moving the metal expands the sleeve a bit and it
should loosen up.

George
